'''Desert Sands''' was an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Desert stormtrooper/Legends|desert stormtrooper]] unit in service with the Galactic Empire during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Characteristics==
[[File:Sandtroopers.jpg|thumb|left|190px|Desert Sands during the search for the stolen Death Star plans]]
The unit was a specialized [[Desert stormtrooper/Legends|desert stormtrooper]] variant with modified armor and equipment to withstand the harsh climates of [[Desert/Legends|desert]] [[Planet/Legends|planets]] like [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], along with heavy weapons, survival gear, and shoulder pauldrons denoting rank. The unit included mounted [[Dewback/Legends|Dewback]] [[Dewback trooper/Legends|troopers]] with its regular contingent.

==History==
{{Quote|We don't need to see his identification.|DSS-0956|<ref name="ANH" />}}
Desert Sands was stationed aboard the [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial I''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Inquisitor (Star Destroyer)|''Inquisitor'']]<ref name="Tinker, Tailor">.{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/source/praji/20090205.html|text=Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Praji|int=Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Praji}}</ref> The unit was headed by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Mod Terrik]],<ref name="WTFWT" /> with his second in command being Senior Officer [[DSS-0956/Legends|DSS-0956]].<ref name="GG1" />

In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], the unit was ordered to land on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] in a [[Sentinel-class landing craft/Legends|''Sentinel''-class landing craft]], tasked with locating [[Tantive IV/Legends|''Tantive IV'']]{{'s}} ejected [[Escape pod/Legends|escape pod]] to recover the stolen [[Death Star plans/Legends|Death Star plans]]. They were split into [[Alvien Squadron|Alvien]], [[Drax Squadron|Drax]] and [[Zeta Squadron (Desert Sands)|Zeta Squadrons]];<ref name="WTFWT" /> accompanied by troops of [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Kosh/Legends|Kosh's]] local garrison.<ref name="VGC7">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iv/explore/visualguides/chp07.html|text=Episode IV Visual Guide &mdash; Chapter 7: Land of the Jawas}}</ref>

[[File:Jundland_Wastes_Final_w.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Zeta Squadron simulating the attack of the sandcrawler by [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Tusken Raiders]].]]
When Desert Sands located and searched the escape pod, the plans were gone. They did however discover a trail leading away from the crashed pod, as well as evidence that the pod's occupants were [[Droid/Legends|droids]]. The troopers followed the trail through the desert, and discovered that [[C-3PO/Legends|one droid]] had been intercepted by a [[Sandcrawler/Legends|Jawa sandcrawler]]. They eventually tracked down the sandcrawler, where they learned that the droids had been sold to [[Owen Lars/Legends|moisture farmers]]. Desert Sands then attacked the sandcrawler, leaving no survivors.<ref name="ANH" />
Desert Sands proceeded on to the moisture farm that had purchased the droids. On arrival, the unit failed to find the droids yet again. They blasted the homestead, and murdered its only inhabitants - [[Owen Lars/Legends|Owen]] and [[Beru Whitesun Lars/Legends|Beru Lars]].<ref name="WTFWT" />

Led by Captain Kosh, the unit attempted to apprehend the droid fugitives in [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], without success. Once the droids escaped the planet in the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], Desert Sands was left on Tatooine to perform clean-up operations.

Soon after the crew of the Falcon escaped, Desert Sands managed to secure Mos Eisley and wipe the rebel presence and their black market operations out of the system.<ref name="SWBF">''[[Star Wars: Battlefront]]''</ref>

